   <body>
      <prereq>
         <indexterm>Independent static bypass switch controller board</indexterm> Tools: PICkit 3 in-circuit debugger.<fig>
            <image href="../Images/pickit_programmer_0000147210.jpg"
                   scalefit="yes"
                   scope="local"
                   placement="inline"/>
         </fig>
      </prereq>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Turn OFF the UPS system. See <xref href="Turn_off_the_UPS_TSK_0000060296.xml"
                     format="dita"
                     scope="local"
                     type="task"/>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Connect the computer to the independent static bypass switch
controller board with the PICkit 3 in-circuit debugger. Do not connect
the PICkit 3 in-circuit debugger directly to the independent static
bypass switch controller board, but use a cable in between. Only connect
to six of the seven pins â€“ see image.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/pickit3_connect_to_only_6_pins_0000149716.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Close the static bypass input breaker Q528. The independent
static bypass switch controller board turns ON (onboard LEDs illuminate).</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig/>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Launch the <uicontrol>MPlab8.73a</uicontrol> software on
your computer.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click on <menucascade>
                  <uicontrol>Configure</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol>Select Device</uicontrol>
               </menucascade>.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen1_0000147209.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the chip model used on the  independent static bypass
switch controller board: <uicontrol>PIC16F876</uicontrol>.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/isbs_controller_chip_model_0000147208.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen2_0000147207.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select <menucascade>
                  <uicontrol>Programme</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol>Select Programmer</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol>PICkit 3</uicontrol>
               </menucascade> (first time).</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/pick3_0000152212.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>The <uicontrol>Mplab</uicontrol> software will perform
a verification of the chip selection.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen3_0000147206.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>If the correct chip <uicontrol>PIC16F876</uicontrol> is selected, the following screen will appeared without any error
message.</p>
                  <stepxmp>
                     <fig>
                        <image href="../Images/mplab_screen4_0000147205.jpg"
                               scalefit="yes"
                               scope="local"
                               placement="inline"/>
                     </fig>
                  </stepxmp>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click on <menucascade>
                  <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol>Import</uicontrol>
               </menucascade> and browse to the latest firmware
file. Select the latest independent static bypass switch controller
board firmware that matches the independent static bypass switch controller
board part number.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen5_0000147234.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen6_0000147233.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen7_0000147232.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click on the <uicontrol>Erase Flash Device</uicontrol> icon
to empty the <uicontrol>PIC16F876</uicontrol> chip memory.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen8_0000147231.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen9_0000147230.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click on the <uicontrol>Blank Check All</uicontrol> icon
to verify that the <uicontrol>PIC16F876</uicontrol> chip is empty.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen10_0000147229.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen11_0000147228.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click on the <uicontrol>Program</uicontrol> icon to write
the latest firmware into the <uicontrol>PIC16F876</uicontrol> chip.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/mplab_screen12_0000147227.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p> The independent static bypass switch controller board
firmware update is complete. Open the static bypass input breaker
Q528 to restart the  independent static bypass switch controller board.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
